The paper deals with modelling choice under uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The use of sets of desirable gambles also suggests a connection to decision making (cs.DM) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA). The paper also presents a set of axioms, which could be relevant to the field of logic and computation (cs.LG).
